title: Zoom Meetings Client (us.zoom.config)
description: This manifest contains the latest settngs for Zoom Meetings Clinet, updated: 07/05/2023 - See this link for more https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/115001799006-Mass-deploying-with-preconfigured-settings-for-macOS (A) These options are only available for devices in the China region. (B) Please have an account admin or owner contact Zoom Support to acquire your account ID. (C) Please have an account admin or owner contact Zoom Support to have this enabled for use. The owner will also need to edit a role to have view/edit access to Device Policy Management. The required token can then be retrieved from the Device Policy Management page.

BlockUntrustedSSLCert.title: BlockUntrustedSSLCert
BlockUntrustedSSLCert.description: Block connections to untrusted SSL certificates. Default: Enabled, 1

AU2_EnableUpdateSuccessNotification.title: AU2 Enable Update Success Notification
AU2_EnableUpdateSuccessNotification.description: Show notification indicating an update has been successfully installed. Default: Enabled, 1

AU2_EnableShowZoomUpdates.title: AU2 Enable Show Zoom Updates
AU2_EnableShowZoomUpdates.description: Show the Zoom Updates section of the General tab in client settings. Depending on if AutoUpdate and SetUpdateChannel are required or not, users may only be able to view this setting. Default: Enabled, 1

NoGoogle.title: NoGoogle
NoGoogle.description: Remove Google login option. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableAudioOverProxy.title: DisableAudioOverProxy
DisableAudioOverProxy.description: Prevent audio traffic over proxies. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_EnablePromptUpdateForAU2.title: AU2 Enable Prompt Update For AU2
AU2_EnablePromptUpdateForAU2.description: Prompt users to update when exiting a meeting or webinar, when an update is available. Default: Disabled. 0

DisableVirtualBkgnd.title: DisableVirtualBkgnd
DisableVirtualBkgnd.description: Disable Virtual Background feature. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_LimitManualUpdateVersion.title: AU2 Limit Manual Update Version
AU2_LimitManualUpdateVersion.description: Allow users to manually check for updates to the desktop client, and if their installed version is lower than the version specified by their update channel (Slow, Fast, custom), they will update to that version instead of the latest version available. This policy is dependent on AU2_EnableAutoUpdate and AU2_EnableManualUpdate policies being enabled. If either is disabled, this policy will fail. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableFaceBeauty.title: EnableFaceBeauty
EnableFaceBeauty.description: Enable Touch up my appearance. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableAlipayLogin.title: EnableAlipayLogin
EnableAlipayLogin.description: Enables login with Alipay authentication. (A)Default: Disabled, 0

ProxyServer.title: ProxyServer
ProxyServer.description: Set a proxy server for desktop client as named proxy. Example: server: port. Default: : Disabled, <empty>

BandwidthLimitUp.title: BandwidthLimitUp
BandwidthLimitUp.description: Set maximum sending bandwidth for the desktop client. Note: If bandwidth is restricted through web settings, the web restrictions override restrictions set in the client. (all values in Kbps)Default: Disabled, <empty>

ProxyBypass.title: ProxyBypass
ProxyBypass.description: Set proxy bypass rule for the desktop client. Default: Disabled, <empty>

AudioAutoAdjust.title: AudioAutoAdjust
AudioAutoAdjust.description: Enable Automatically adjust microphone volume audio setting. Default: Enabled, 1

Intercloud_DisableAllFeatures.title: Intercloud_DisableAllFeatures
Intercloud_DisableAllFeatures.description: Disables all features except for audio and video for meetings hosted on the ZfG cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

Intercloud_DisableWhiteBoard.title: Intercloud_DisableWhiteBoard
Intercloud_DisableWhiteBoard.description: Disables the use of in-meeting whiteboarding on meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableShareVideo.title: EnableShareVideo
EnableShareVideo.description: Enable the Optimize for video clip option when sharing. Default: Enabled, 1

Intercloud_DisableClosedCaptioning.title: Intercloud_DisableClosedCaptioning
Intercloud_DisableClosedCaptioning.description: Disabled by default, this option disables the use of captioning features on meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableLightAdaption.title: EnableLightAdaption
EnableLightAdaption.description: Enable Adjust for low-light video setting. Default: Disabled, 0

RecordPath.title: RecordPath
RecordPath.description: Set the default recording location for local recordings. Default: /Users/User Name/Documents/Zoom

Intercloud_DisableRemoteControl.title: Intercloud_DisableRemoteControl
Intercloud_DisableRemoteControl.description: Disabled by default, this option disables the remote control of shared screens in meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_UpdateChannelCandidates.title: AU2 Update Channel Candidates
AU2_UpdateChannelCandidates.description: Define additional update channel options. The format should follow <channel ID>:<channel name>, with multiple channels separated by a semicolon. For example: 0:Slow;1:Fast;3:Custom Channel Any custom channels must be created in the web portal and require the user be authenticated before the custom channel is recognized, otherwise the Slow channel will be used by default. The default Slow and Fast tracks are always available, even if not included in the policy string. Default: (empty)

DisableDaemonInstall.title: DisableDaemonInstall
DisableDaemonInstall.description: Controls the use of the daemon helper to install updates, which bypasses the need to enter admin credentials when upgrading. This option requires AutoUpdate option to be enabled, and will fail if not enabled. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableZoomApps.title: DisableZoomApps
DisableZoomApps.description: Hide the Zoom Apps button. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableClosedCaptioning.title: DisableClosedCaptioning
DisableClosedCaptioning.description: Disable the use of all closed captioning. Default: Disabled, 0

zAutoJoinVoip.title: zAutoJoinVoip
zAutoJoinVoip.description: Automatically connect audio with computer audio when joining a meeting. Default: Disabled, 0

MeshMulticastPort.title: MeshMulticastPort
MeshMulticastPort.description: When utilizing Zoom Mesh, this policy allows an admin to specify a valid port to be used as the UDP multicast port to communicate with other Zoom Mesh nodes on the network. Default: Port 36699, 0

DisableMeeting3rdPartyFileStorage.title: DisableMeeting3rdPartyFileStorage
DisableMeeting3rdPartyFileStorage.description: Disable in-meeting 3rd party file transfer. Default: Disabled, 0

ShowConnectedTime.title: ShowConnectedTime
ShowConnectedTime.description: Enable the Show Meeting Timers setting. This setting allows for viewing the current duration of the meeting, or the remaining time, based on scheduled duration. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableHardwareOptimizeVideoSharing.title: EnableHardwareOptimizeVideoSharing
EnableHardwareOptimizeVideoSharing.description: Use hardware acceleration to optimize video sharing. Default: Enabled, 1

SetFaceBeautyValue.title: SetFaceBeautyValue
SetFaceBeautyValue.description: Used in conjunction with EnableFaceBeauty, this allows you to set the exact intensity of the Touch up my appearance filter. Default: Disabled, 25

DisableManualClosedCaptioning.title: DisableManualClosedCaptioning
DisableManualClosedCaptioning.description: Disable the use of manual, user-entered captioning. Default: Disabled, 0

SetUseSystemDefaultSpeakerForVOIP.title: SetUseSystemDefaultSpeakerForVOIP
SetUseSystemDefaultSpeakerForVOIP.description: Use the default system microphone. Default: Disabled, 0

HidePhoneInComingCallWhileInMeeting.title: HidePhoneInComingCallWhileInMeeting
HidePhoneInComingCallWhileInMeeting.description: Prevent incoming call notifications while in a meeting. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_EnableManualUpdate.title: AU2 Enable Manual Update
AU2_EnableManualUpdate.description: Control the visibility of the Check for Updates option in the client. Default: Enabled, 1

EnableWeChatLogin.title: EnableWeChatLogin
EnableWeChatLogin.description: Enables login with WeChat authentication (A). Default: Disabled, 0

zDisableVideo.title: zDisableVideo
zDisableVideo.description: Automatically turn off camera when joining a meeting. Default: Disabled, 0

MeshListenPortRange.title: MeshListenPortRange
MeshListenPortRange.description: When utilizing Zoom Mesh, this policy allows a valid port range to be used to set up listen sockets for connection requests between Mesh parents and children nodes. The nodes will also use this range to send signals and media data. Default: 18801-19800, (empty)

MuteWhenLockScreen.title: MuteWhenLockScreen
MuteWhenLockScreen.description: Automatically mute the microphone and turn off video, when the screen is locked during a meeting. Default: : Enabled, 1

DisableVideoFilters.title: DisableVideoFilters
DisableVideoFilters.description: Disable Video filters feature. Default: Disabled, 0

SetSuppressBackgroundNoiseLevel.title: SetSuppressBackgroundNoiseLevel
SetSuppressBackgroundNoiseLevel.description: Set level of background noise suppression: 0 - Auto 1- Low 2 - Medium 3 - High. Default: : Auto (0)

token.title: token
token.description: Enroll your device into Zoom Device Management with a token provided from the web portal. Default: <empty>

EnablQQLogin.title: EnablQQLogin
EnablQQLogin.description: Enables login with QQ authentication. (A)Default: Disabled, 0

DisableMeetingReactions.title: DisableMeetingReactions
DisableMeetingReactions.description: Disable the use of Meeting reactions. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableEmbedBrowserForSSO.title: EnableEmbedBrowserForSSO
EnableEmbedBrowserForSSO.description: Use embedded browser in the client for SSO. Default: Disabled, 0

Account.title: Account
Account.description: Restrict the client to only join meetings hosted by the specified account IDs. (B)Default:  Disabled, (empty)

DisableKeepSignedInWithGoogle.title: DisableKeepSignedInWithGoogle
DisableKeepSignedInWithGoogle.description: Require fresh Google login upon client start. Default: Disabled, 0

zDisableAnnotation.title: zDisableAnnotation
zDisableAnnotation.description: Disable and remove the ability to annotate over shared screen. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableDoNotDisturbInSharing.title: EnableDoNotDisturbInSharing
EnableDoNotDisturbInSharing.description: Silence system notifications when sharing desktop. Default: Enabled, 1

EnableIndependentDataPort.title: EnableIndependentDataPort
EnableIndependentDataPort.description: If enabled, the client will use the following ports for media transmission: Audio: 8803 Screen share: 8802 Video: 8801. Default: : Disabled, 0

EnableHIDControl.title: EnableHIDControl
EnableHIDControl.description: Enables HID control of USB devices by the Zoom client. Default: Enabled, 1

MeshMulticastIP.title: MeshMulticastIP
MeshMulticastIP.description: When utilizing Zoom Mesh, this policy allows admins to specify a valid IP address to be a UDP multicast IP for Zoom apps to declare themselves and detect each other in their local sub-network (255.255.255.0). Admins can choose other IP addresses within the range of [224.0.0.1, 239.255.255.255]. Default: 224.0.0.1, (empty)

ShowProfilePhotosInChat.title: ShowProfilePhotosInChat
ShowProfilePhotosInChat.description: Controls if user profile pictures are shown in Zoom Chat. Default: Enabled, 1

DisableWhiteBoard.title: DisableWhiteBoard
DisableWhiteBoard.description: Disable Classic Whiteboard feature. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableAutoReverseVirtualBkgnd.title: EnableAutoReverseVirtualBkgnd
EnableAutoReverseVirtualBkgnd.description: Require post-meeting virtual background auto-reversal. Default: Disabled, 0

EmbedUserAgentString.title: EmbedUserAgentString
EmbedUserAgentString.description: Embed a specified user agent string for all HTTP requests from Zoom client. Default: Disabled, (empty)

AU2_SetUpdateChannel.title: AU2 Set Update Channel
AU2_SetUpdateChannel.description: Set the cadence of updates applied to the desktop client: Slow (0): fewer updates and better stability. Fast (1): newest features and updates. Default: Slow (0)

EnableCloudSwitch.title: EnableCloudSwitch
EnableCloudSwitch.description: Enable the option to switch between Zoom commercial (default) and Zoom for Gov. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableSpotlightSelf.title: EnableSpotlightSelf
EnableSpotlightSelf.description: Show self as the active speaker when speaking. Default: Disabled, 0

OverrideEnforceSigninIntercloud.title: OverrideEnforceSigninIntercloud
OverrideEnforceSigninIntercloud.description: Override the EnforceSignInToJoin policy and allows a user to join a Zoom meeting hosted on the ZfG Cloud, without the need to authenticate. Default: Disabled, 0

Login_Domain.title: Login_Domain
Login_Domain.description: Set the email address domain that users can login with, each separated by &. Example: zoom.us & hooli.com Note: The & must be entered as an escape character &, or use CDATA to wrap the entire string. This only applies to plist mass deployment. Default: Disabled, (empty)

SetWebDomain.title: SetWebDomain
SetWebDomain.description: Sets the web domain for logging in or joining a meeting. By default, the value is https://zoom.us or https://zoom.com. Default: Disabled, (empty)

EnableMirrorEffect.title: EnableMirrorEffect
EnableMirrorEffect.description: Enable mirroring of your video. Mirror effect only affects your view of your video. Default: Enabled, 1

DisableSlideControl.title: DisableSlideControl
DisableSlideControl.description: Disable Slide Control feature. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_InstallAtIdleTime.title: AU2 Install At Idle Time
AU2_InstallAtIdleTime.description: Auto install an available update when the device is idle. Idle devices must be:No current meeting, phone call, or contact center engagement. No upcoming meeting within 30 minutes Screen is locked or screen saver is active. Default: : Disabled, 1

ProxyPAC.title: ProxyPAC
ProxyPAC.description: Set proxy server for desktop client with PAC URL. Default: Disabled, <empty>

your_recording_path.title: your_recording_path
your_recording_path.description: Set the default recording location for local recordings. Default: /Users/User Name/Documents/Zoom

your_pac_url.title: your_pac_url
your_pac_url.description: Set proxy server for desktop client with PAC URL. Default: Disabled, <empty>

SetScreenCaptureMode.title: SetScreenCaptureMode
SetScreenCaptureMode.description: Set the screen capture mode: 0 - Auto 1 - Legacy operating systems 2 - Share with window filtering 3 - Advanced share with window filtering 4 - Advanced share without window. Default: : Auto, 0

DisableDirectConnection2Web.title: DisableDirectConnection2Web
DisableDirectConnection2Web.description: Disable all direct connections to Zoom web service. Default: Disabled, 0

proxy_address.title: proxy_address
proxy_address.description: Set a proxy server for desktop client as named proxy. Example: server: port. Default: : Disabled, <empty>

Intercloud_DisableComputerAudio.title: Intercloud_DisableComputerAudio
Intercloud_DisableComputerAudio.description: Disabled by default, this option disables the use of computer audio for connecting to meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

HideSelfView.title: HideSelfView
HideSelfView.description: Controls the use of the Hide Self View option. Default: : Disabled, 0

zUse720PByDefault.title: zUse720PByDefault
zUse720PByDefault.description: Use HD video in meetings. Default: Disabled, 0

ClickToCallDefault.title: ClickToCallDefault
ClickToCallDefault.description: Choose which Zoom service is used when clicking a phone number to place a call. 0 - Zoom Phone 1 - Zoom Contact Center. Default: : Zoom Phone, 0

MuteVoipWhenJoin.title: MuteVoipWhenJoin
MuteVoipWhenJoin.description: Mute computer audio microphone when joining a meeting. Default: Disabled, 0

ConfirmWhenLeave.title: ConfirmWhenLeave
ConfirmWhenLeave.description: Confirm before leaving a meeting. Default: Enabled, 1

EnforceAppSignInToJoin.title: EnforceAppSignInToJoin
EnforceAppSignInToJoin.description: Require authentication on the desktop client to join any meeting on the desktop client. Default: Disabled, 0

SetMessengerDoNotDropThread.title: SetMessengerDoNotDropThread
SetMessengerDoNotDropThread.description: Move messages with new replies to the bottom of the chat/channel. Default: Enabled, 1

DisableInMeetingWhiteBoard.title: DisableInMeetingWhiteBoard
DisableInMeetingWhiteBoard.description: Disable the Zoom Whiteboard feature in meetings and webinars. Default: Disabled, 0

ShowIMMessagePreview.title: ShowIMMessagePreview
ShowIMMessagePreview.description: Allow message previews in system notifications when a chat message is received. Default: Enabled. 1

EnforceSignInToJoin.title: EnforceSignInToJoin
EnforceSignInToJoin.description: Require users to be authenticated before joining a meeting with the desktop client.  Authentication can take place through the the web portal, if joining through join URL. Default: Disabled, 0

FullScreenWhenJoin.title: FullScreenWhenJoin
FullScreenWhenJoin.description: When starting or joining a meeting, the meeting window will enter full-screen. Default: Disabled, 0

ShowVideoMessageButton.title: ShowVideoMessageButton
ShowVideoMessageButton.description: Allow use of the Send video message option. Default: Enabled, 1

SetUpdatingChannel.title: SetUpdatingChannel
SetUpdatingChannel.description: Control the cadence of updates applied to the desktop client on versions between 5.8.6 and 5.10.1: Slow (0): fewer updates and better stability. Fast (1): newest features and updates. Please see AutoUpdate section for important details. Default: : Slow, 0

zHideNoVideoUser.title: zHideNoVideoUser
zHideNoVideoUser.description: Hide non-video participants by default. Default: Disabled, 0

zAutoFullScreenWhenViewShare.title: zAutoFullScreenWhenViewShare
zAutoFullScreenWhenViewShare.description: When viewing shared content, the content window automatically goes fullscreen. Default: Enabled, 1

EnableLaunchApp4IncomingCalls.title: EnableLaunchApp4IncomingCalls
EnableLaunchApp4IncomingCalls.description: Control the Launch an external app or a URL for incoming calls option in the client. This must be used in coordination with SetCommand4IncomingCalls, so that the URL can be configured as well. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableGuestMesh.title: EnableGuestMesh
EnableGuestMesh.description: When utilizing Zoom Mesh, this allows external users (not on your account) to join a Webinar through the local Zoom Mesh-enabled network. Other requirements must be met, such as the device having the minimum supported client version for Mesh connections and the associated account setting in the web portal also enabled. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableSideCar.title: DisableSideCar
DisableSideCar.description: Disable the use of Webinar Resources, which allows webinar hosts with the ability to link to external resources, such as newsletter sign-ups, learn more pages, and others. Default: Disabled, 0

NoFacebook.title: NoFacebook
NoFacebook.description: Remove Facebook login option. Default: Disabled, 0

your account ID.title: your account ID
your account ID.description: Restrict the client to only join meetings hosted by the specified account IDs. (B)Default: Disabled, (empty)

EnforceSignInToJoinForWebinar.title: EnforceSignInToJoinForWebinar
EnforceSignInToJoinForWebinar.description: Require users to be authenticated before joining a webinar with the desktop client.  Authentication can take place through the the web portal, if joining through join URL. Default: Disabled, 0

zRemoteControllAllApp.title: zRemoteControllAllApp
zRemoteControllAllApp.description: Allow remote control of all applications. Default: Enabled, 1

SetLightAdaptionManualValue.title: SetLightAdaptionManualValue
SetLightAdaptionManualValue.description: Used in conjunction with EnableLightAdaption, this allows you to set the exact intensity of the low-light adjustment. Default: Disabled, 20

DisableKeepSignedInWithSSO.title: DisableKeepSignedInWithSSO
DisableKeepSignedInWithSSO.description: Require fresh SSO login upon client start. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableNonVerbalFeedback.title: DisableNonVerbalFeedback
DisableNonVerbalFeedback.description: Disable the use of Non-verbal feedback. Default: Disabled, 0

Intercloud_DisableMeetingChat.title: Intercloud_DisableMeetingChat
Intercloud_DisableMeetingChat.description: Disables the use of in-meeting chat on meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

PlaySoundForIMMessage.title: PlaySoundForIMMessage
PlaySoundForIMMessage.description: Play audio notifications when an IM message is received. Default: Enabled, 1

DisableDesktopShare.title: DisableDesktopShare
DisableDesktopShare.description: Disable the option to share your desktop when screen sharing. Default: Disabled, 0

Intercloud_DisableMeetingPolls.title: Intercloud_DisableMeetingPolls
Intercloud_DisableMeetingPolls.description: Disabled by default, this option disables the use of polling in meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

zAutoUpdate.title: zAutoUpdate
zAutoUpdate.description: Enable updates through the client by users. When disabled, the Check for Updates button is also hidden. Please see AutoUpdate section for important details. Default: Disabled, 0

Intercloud_DisableLocalRecording.title: Intercloud_DisableLocalRecording
Intercloud_DisableLocalRecording.description: Disabled by default, this option disables the ability to locally record meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableWinExtendProtectedAuth.title: EnableWinExtendProtectedAuth
EnableWinExtendProtectedAuth.description: Enable to Support Windows Extended Protection with NTLM authentication. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableSharingOverProxy.title: DisableSharingOverProxy
DisableSharingOverProxy.description: Prevent screen sharing traffic over proxies. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableShareClipboardWhenRemoteControl.title: EnableShareClipboardWhenRemoteControl
EnableShareClipboardWhenRemoteControl.description: Allow clipboard access during remote control. Default: Disabled, 0

DefaultUsePortraitView.title: DefaultUsePortraitView
DefaultUsePortraitView.description: Default to Portrait Mode upon opening Zoom. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableQnA.title: DisableQnA
DisableQnA.description: Disable the use of Q&A in webinars. Default: Disabled, 0

Intercloud_DisableMeetingReactions.title: Intercloud_DisableMeetingReactions
Intercloud_DisableMeetingReactions.description: Disables the use of meeting reactions on meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. Default: Disabled, 0

zDisableFT.title: zDisableFT
zDisableFT.description: Disable in-meeting file transfer. (sending or receiving)Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_EnableUpdateAvailableBanner.title: AU2 Enable Update Available Banner
AU2_EnableUpdateAvailableBanner.description: Show the Update Available banner on the Home tab of the client, when an update is available. Default: Enabled, 1

ShowVoiceMessageButton.title: ShowVoiceMessageButton
ShowVoiceMessageButton.description: Allow use of the Send audio message option. Default: Enabled, 1

Intercloud_DisableShareScreen.title: Intercloud_DisableShareScreen
Intercloud_DisableShareScreen.description: Disables the local ability to share screen on meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. This does not affect others ability to shared content. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableDiagnostic.title: EnableDiagnostic
EnableDiagnostic.description: Controls the ability for the desktop client to access the Network Connectivity Tool, which allows a user to test their network connection with Zoom services. Default: Enabled, 1

DisableAutoLaunchSSO.title: DisableAutoLaunchSSO
DisableAutoLaunchSSO.description: Prevent Zoom from automatically launching the previously used SSO URL. This is useful for users with multiple accounts, each having their own SSO URL. Default: Disabled, 0

BandwidthLimitDown.title: BandwidthLimitDown
BandwidthLimitDown.description: Set maximum receiving bandwidth for the desktop client. Note: If bandwidth is restricted through web settings, the web restrictions override restrictions set in the client. (all values in Kbps)Default: Disabled, <empty>

SetCommand4IncomingCalls.title: SetCommand4IncomingCalls
SetCommand4IncomingCalls.description: Set the URL used when the client receives an incoming call. This must be used in coordination with EnableLaunchApp4IncomingCalls. Default: Disabled, (empty)

Intercloud_DisableAnnotation.title: Intercloud_DisableAnnotation
Intercloud_DisableAnnotation.description: Disables the local ability to annotate on shared content in meetings hosted on the ZfG Cloud. This does not affect others ability to annotate. Default: Disabled, 0

zDualMonitorOn.title: zDualMonitorOn
zDualMonitorOn.description: Enable dual monitor mode. Default: Disabled, 0

NotifyCMRAvailable.title: NotifyCMRAvailable
NotifyCMRAvailable.description: Control the desktop client setting Show notifications when a new recording is available. Default: Enabled, 1

EnableAutoLightAdaption.title: EnableAutoLightAdaption
EnableAutoLightAdaption.description: Set mode of adjusting low-light video feature. This is dependent on the EnableLightAdaption option. 1 - Auto 0 - Manual. Default: : Auto, 1

Enable49Video.title: Enable49Video
Enable49Video.description: Set max number of participants displayed in Gallery View to 49 participants per screen. Default: Disabled, 0

MuteIMNotificationWhenInMeeting.title: MuteIMNotificationWhenInMeeting
MuteIMNotificationWhenInMeeting.description: Mute chat system notifications when in a meeting. Default: Enabled, 1

EmbedDeviceTag.title: EmbedDeviceTag
EmbedDeviceTag.description: Embed a specified device tag string for all HTTP requests from Zoom client application. This string will be appended to the head of the regular HTTP requests. Default: Disabled, (empty)

ForceSSOURL.title: ForceSSOURL
ForceSSOURL.description: Set and lock the default SSO URL for SSO login. For example, hooli.zoom.us would be set as ForceSSOUrl=hooli. Default: Disabled, (empty)

KeepSignedIn.title: KeepSignedIn
KeepSignedIn.description: Keep the user signed in to the client when relaunched. (Email login only) Default: Disabled, 0

zAutoSSOLogin.title: zAutoSSOLogin
zAutoSSOLogin.description: Defaults login to SSO. Default: Disabled, 0

PresentToRoomOptimizeVideo.title: PresentToRoomOptimizeVideo
PresentToRoomOptimizeVideo.description: Optimize screen sharing for video clip when sharing to a Zoom Room. Default: Enabled, 1

PresentToRoomOption.title: PresentToRoomOption
PresentToRoomOption.description: Set sharing option when sharing to a Zoom Room: 0 - Show all sharing options 1 - Automatically share desktopDefaut: Automatically share desktop, 1

DisableDirectShare.title: DisableDirectShare
DisableDirectShare.description: Disable direct share with Zoom Rooms option. Default: : Disabled, 0

EnablePhoneLogin.title: EnablePhoneLogin
EnablePhoneLogin.description: Enables login with phone authentication. (A)Default: Disabled, 0

SetEnrollToken4CloudMDM.title: SetEnrollToken4CloudMDM
SetEnrollToken4CloudMDM.description: Enroll your device into Zoom Device Management with a token provided from the web portal. Default: <empty>

SetUseSystemDefaultMicForVOIP.title: SetUseSystemDefaultMicForVOIP
SetUseSystemDefaultMicForVOIP.description: Use the default system speakers. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_EnableAutoUpdate.title: AU2 Enable AutoUpdate
AU2_EnableAutoUpdate.description: Enable auto updates through the client. Disabling this policy also disables the following AU2 policies: AU2_SetUpdateChannel AU2_LimitManualUpdateVersion AU2_DeploySpecificVersion AU2_SetUpdateSchedule AU2_InstallAtIdleTime AU2_SafeUpgradePeriod. Default: : Enabled, 1

bypass_rule.title: bypass_rule
bypass_rule.description: Set proxy bypass rule for the desktop client. Default: Disabled, <empty>

VideoRenderMethod.title: VideoRenderMethod
VideoRenderMethod.description: Set the video rendering method: 0 - Auto 1 - Direct3D11 Flip Mode 2 - Direct3D11 3 - Direct3D9 4 - GDI. Default: : Auto, 0

IgnoreBandwidthLimits.title: IgnoreBandwidthLimits
IgnoreBandwidthLimits.description: Ignore bandwidth limit set on web settings. (Useful for exceptions to bandwidth restrictions)Default: Disabled, 0

DisableScreenShare.title: DisableScreenShare
DisableScreenShare.description: Disable the ability to share your screen in meetings and webinars. Note: This does not disable incoming screen sharing from other participants. Default: Disabled, 0

PresentInMeetingOption.title: PresentInMeetingOption
PresentInMeetingOption.description: Set sharing option when sharing your screen within a meeting: 0 - Show all sharing options 1 - Automatically share desktop. Default: : Show all sharing options, 0

DisableVideoOverProxy.title: DisableVideoOverProxy
DisableVideoOverProxy.description: Prevent video traffic over proxies. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableZoomAppsGuestAccess.title: DisableZoomAppsGuestAccess
DisableZoomAppsGuestAccess.description: Control the ability for users to utilize a Zoom App in Guest mode. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_SetUpdateSchedule.title: AU2 Set Update Schedule
AU2_SetUpdateSchedule.description: Set to download an available update version. Update is then initiated by the user through prompt, or during idle time or the specified safe upgrade period.Values are formatted as HHMM-HHMM, such that 1:00 to 2:30 is coded as 0100-0230. Time frames spanning into the next day are supported, such as 1800-0400 meaning 18:00 to 04:00 the next day. Default: (empty)

EnableRemindMeetingTime.title: EnableRemindMeetingTime
EnableRemindMeetingTime.description: Display reminder notifications for upcoming meetings. Default: Disabled, 0

EnableShareAudio.title: EnableShareAudio
EnableShareAudio.description: Enable the Share computer audio option when sharing. Default: Enabled, 1

zSSOHost.title: zSSOHost
zSSOHost.description: Set the default SSO URL for SSO login. For example, hooli.zoom.us would be set as zSSOHost=hooli. Default: Disabled, (empty)

EnableAppleLogin.title: EnableAppleLogin
EnableAppleLogin.description: Allow access to Apple login option. Default: Enabled, 1

DisableWebinarReactions.title: DisableWebinarReactions
DisableWebinarReactions.description: Disable the use of Webinar Reactions. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableComputerAudio.title: DisableComputerAudio
DisableComputerAudio.description: Disable and remove the Computer Audio from the meeting audio options. Default: Disabled, 0

DisableLoginWithEmail.title: DisableLoginWithEmail
DisableLoginWithEmail.description: Remove Email login option. Default: Disabled, 0

AU2_SafeUpgradePeriod.title: AU2 Safe Upgrade Period
AU2_SafeUpgradePeriod.description: Set to install updates within a given time period. This policy depends on AU2_InstallAtIdleTime being enabled.Values are formatted as HHMM-HHMM, such that 1:00 to 2:30 is coded as 0100-0230. Time frames spanning into the next day are supported, such as 1800-0400 meaning 18:00 to 04:00 the next day. Default: 0000-0400 (Midnight-4:00)

EnableOriginalSound.title: EnableOriginalSound
EnableOriginalSound.description: Enable the Original sound for musicians audio profile for the meeting audio input. Default: Disabled, 0

PresentToRoomWithAudio.title: PresentToRoomWithAudio
PresentToRoomWithAudio.description: Share sound when screen sharing to a Zoom Room. Default: Enabled, 1

Intercloud_DisableMeetingFileTransfer.title: Intercloud_DisableMeetingFileTransfer
